subjective.hpi: Patient presents with 3 days of watery diarrhea without blood, 6 bowel movements per day, associated with left lower quadrant crampy intermittent pain without radiation. Day 1 had bilious vomiting without hematemesis and fever, but no vomiting since. Patient reports lethargy and weakness. Had Chinese takeaway 4 days ago; rest of family (wife and children) had vomiting but no diarrhea. No other known contacts with similar illness.

procedures_ordered: Review in 3-5 days if not better
plan.patient_instructions: Conservative management with rest and push fluids. Take paracetamol if fever develops. Use over-the-counter Dioralyte for rehydration. Return for review in 3-5 days if not improving, or earlier if symptoms worsen.
